		<pb n="1"/>
          <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName>&#44; <date>April 6<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1848</date></p>
          <p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">DSir&#33;</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">I beg have to inform you<lb/> that at the annual Meeting of the Hebrew Benevolent Associa&#45;<lb/>tion of <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>&#44; held on <date>Sunday March 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi>1848</date>&#44;<lb/> the following Officers&#44; were elected to serve for the ensuing<lb/> year.</p>
          <list type="members">
            <head>List of members</head>
            <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>A Emanuel.</persName> President.<persName>M Kursheedt </persName> Vice President</item>
            <item rend="indent(1)"><persName>David Sanger.</persName> Treasurer. And <persName>Leopold Cohn</persName> Secretary</item> 
          </list>
          <p>Board of Managers&#8212;<persName>S. Magner</persName>. <persName>A Harber</persName>&#44; <persName>E. Jacobs</persName>. <persName>G G Levi</persName><lb/> and <persName>N. Worms</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">The anniversary Ball&#44; given in this city on the <date>20<hi rend="sup">th</hi><lb/> March 1848.</date> for the benefit of the association&#44; was very num&#45;<lb/>erously attended many distinguished citizens&#44; and dignitaries<lb/> of the state were present on the&#44; Occasion&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">It is gratifying to state&#44; that the affair passed<lb/> off to the entire <sic>satisfactione</sic> of all&#44; and much praise<lb/> is due to the <hi rend="underline">committee of arrangement</hi>&#44; for the<lb/> Splendor and style in which the ball was conducted<lb/> and their untiring efforts&#44; to give general satisfaction&#44;<lb/> has been crowned with great success. <sic>the</sic> nett proceeds<lb/> amounting to Seven Hundred dollars which amount<lb/> greatly replenishes the exhausted state of the fund of<lb/> the Society&#44; having expended for charitable purposes<lb/> Fifteen Hundred Dollars during the passed year.</p>
    <pb n="2"/>
          <p>caused by the raging Epidemic of last summer.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have the honor to remain with sentiments of esteem</p>
          <p rend="indent(5)">Your Very Obt Sevt</p>
          <p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">L. Cohn</persName></p>
          <p rend="indent(6)">Secretary H. B. A.</p>
          
